Sea freight corresponds to average international freight charges per tonne. Passenger air transport corresponds to average airline
revenue per passenger mile until 2000 spliced to US import air passenger fares afterwards. International calls correspond to cost of
a three-minute call from New York to London.
Data source: Transaction Costs - OECD Economic Outlook (2007)
